Package it.polimi.ingsw.Model.Resources

Class ResQuantity

java.lang.Object
it.polimi.ingsw.Model.Resources.ResQuantity
public class ResQuantity
extends java.lang.Object
This class associates a quantity to a resource. The instances of ResQuantity are immutable.

  • Method Details

    • createReqMap

      public static java.util.Map<Resource,​java.lang.Integer> createReqMap​(Board board, java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Integer> shelves, java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Integer> quantity, java.util.ArrayList<ResQuantity> strongbox) throws InvalidActionException
      This method creates a map with key Resource and value Integer which contains a summary of all the resources selected and checks if they are effectively present in the warehouse and in the strongbox.
      Parameters:
      board - the board of the player
      shelves - ArrayList of Integer which represents all the shelves from which to get the resources
      quantity - ArrayList of Integer which represents the amount of resources to be removed from each shelf
      strongbox - ArrayList of ResQuantity which represents all the resources to be taken from the StrongBox It is important that each resource is present at most once
      Returns:
      a Map with key Resource and value Integer
      Throws:
      InvalidActionException - if the resources selected are more than the resources effectively present.

    • useResources

      public static boolean useResources​(Board board, java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Integer> shelves, java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Integer> quantity, java.util.ArrayList<ResQuantity> strongbox) throws InvalidActionException
      This method subtracts (according to the input parameters) from the warehouse and the strongBox the resources selected. It is required that the resources selected are effectively present in the warehouse and strongbox.
      Parameters:
      board - the board of the player
      shelves - ArrayList of Integer which represents all the shelves from which to subtract the resources
      quantity - ArrayList of Integer which represents the amount of resources to be removed from each shelf
      strongbox - ArrayList of ResQuantity which represents all the resources to be subtracted from the StrongBox
      Returns:
      true if the operation ends correctly
      Throws:
      InvalidActionException - if the resources selected are more than the resources effectively present.

    • checkDevelopment

      public void checkDevelopment​(java.util.Map<Resource,​java.lang.Integer> resourceStatus, Board board) throws InvalidActionException
      This method checks if there are enough resources in the Map passed as parameter(considering the eventual discount). If the resources in the Map are enough it modifies the Map and subtract those resources, otherwise it throws an InvalidActionException
      Parameters:
      resourceStatus - the map on which operations are done
      board - the board of the player
      Throws:
      InvalidActionException - if the resources in the map are enough
